Some whitebarks have genetic resistance to blister rust .
Since 1983 , the bear population has roughly tripled to 600 animals roaming the 5.8 million acre recovery zone .
The whitebark pine nut weighs in at a thin fraction of an ounce .
Wandering grizzlies can terrorize rural neighborhoods , chew up a rancher 's calves and occasionally maul people .
Rich newcomers build palatial homes on steep mountain slopes ( many in areas thick with grizzlies ) , frequent organic dry cleaners and insist on fresh seafood at pricey restaurants .
